headline: Prediction: 2 Stocks That'll Be Worth More Than Pepsi and Starbucks 5 Years From Now
summary: Not only does it own its namesake Pepsi brand, which was launched under the Pepsi-Cola name in 1898, but it also owns big-name brands such as Mountain Dew, Lay's potato chips, Gatorade, Doritos, Tostitos, Quaker Oats, and more.  Pepsi has been in business for more than a century and has a market capitalization surpassing $200 billion.  For its part, coffee giant Starbucks hasn't been in business quite as long -- it opened its doors in 1971.
